\p{As [before](stt-00CY), we had to adapt the proof from \citek{RS17}
to make lesser use of extension types. Fortunately, there
is a nice argument that involves [the join-slice adjunction](stt-00D5).
In the simplicial setting, we have that the cone of the 1-simplex
#{1 * \Delta^1} is equivalent to #{\Delta^2}; in our more general
setting (where we don't assume #{I} to be totally ordered) this
is not an equivalence, but a simplicial equivalence. This nicely
breaks apart the proof into first showing that \em{any} type is
local wrt. the inclusion #{\Lambda^2_1 \to 1 * \Delta^1} (called
being [(left) strong Segal](stt-00DA)) iff #{\Hom(x,-)} is covariant.
 We can then separately show that [simplicial types are Strong Segal
iff they are Segal](stt-00DG).}
